The paper discusses a clustering algorithm, specifically the K-means algorithm, and proposes a new initialization method based on discriminant analysis. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments on diverse data sets, which suggests a focus on data mining (cs.DM). Additionally, the use of hierarchical clustering and PCA suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
